274
00:17:05.304 --> 00:17:08.505
Ji Ho, wear the dress I got you when you meet his parents.

275
00:17:08.505 --> 00:17:09.544
Okay?

276
00:17:12.215 --> 00:17:14.485
I know this can sound weird,

277
00:17:15.084 --> 00:17:17.884
but I'm sorry to get married...

278
00:17:18.314 --> 00:17:20.655
at this moment.

279
00:17:24.755 --> 00:17:26.354
I knew it.

280
00:17:28.695 --> 00:17:31.394
Just feel sorry until today, okay?

281
00:17:36.735 --> 00:17:39.874
Why would she feel sorry? It's not like she's marrying my husband.

282
00:17:40.175 --> 00:17:41.544
How innocent of her.

283
00:17:44.044 --> 00:17:46.215
Hey, you've never seen him, right?

284
00:17:46.374 --> 00:17:47.544
Who are you talking about?

285
00:17:47.985 --> 00:17:49.084
Ji Ho's husband.

286
00:17:49.544 --> 00:17:50.784
You know nothing in detail, do you?

287
00:17:51.455 --> 00:17:52.715
How would I know?

288
00:17:54.824 --> 00:17:57.425
We have to know in details about him before they get married.

289
00:17:58.155 --> 00:18:00.064
That innocent Ji Ho isn't marrying some scammer, is she?

290
00:18:00.294 --> 00:18:02.294
Let's ask Won Seok when he comes back.

291
00:18:03.064 --> 00:18:05.094
He must know a lot about him.

292
00:18:08.364 --> 00:18:09.405
What is it?

293
00:18:10.275 --> 00:18:11.775
Are you two still fighting?

294
00:18:14.205 --> 00:18:17.475
He hasn't come home for five days already.

295
00:18:20.915 --> 00:18:22.284
You can't return it?

296
00:18:22.685 --> 00:18:25.614
They'll never take it back.

297
00:18:32.124 --> 00:18:33.364
Aren't you going home?

298
00:18:33.425 --> 00:18:36.394
I drank 23 bottles of soju for the past 3 days.

299
00:18:36.634 --> 00:18:39.905
I feel like my organs are destroyed and my lever melted down.

300
00:18:39.905 --> 00:18:43.005
I can only go back if I have home. Where can I go back to?

301
00:18:43.405 --> 00:18:46.074
Go back to the rooftop house you got under your name...

302
00:18:46.074 --> 00:18:47.705
but with your girlfriend's deposit.

303
00:18:47.844 --> 00:18:50.475
I'm not going back! I'm really upset this time.

304
00:18:50.814 --> 00:18:52.574
Do you know how hard I tried to get that sofa?

305
00:18:52.574 --> 00:18:56.185
I sold that wireless keyboard I love to the secondhand shop.

306
00:18:56.314 --> 00:18:59.314
Why was she so upset though?

307
00:18:59.354 --> 00:19:01.624
You bought the sofa she wanted.

308
00:19:01.624 --> 00:19:04.425
If sofa's not the answer, then what is?

309
00:19:05.394 --> 00:19:07.794
I don't know. How can I keep up with her temperament?

310
00:19:09.794 --> 00:19:12.564
Or could it be something else...

311
00:19:12.695 --> 00:19:14.405
other than the sofa?

312
00:19:16.804 --> 00:19:18.804
I can't believe he really got you this sofa.

313
00:19:19.235 --> 00:19:20.874
Won Seok's so...

314
00:19:22.175 --> 00:19:24.175
pure. He's really innocent.

315
00:19:26.915 --> 00:19:30.155
Gosh, but this sofa is great.

316
00:19:32.915 --> 00:19:34.255
He really is pure.

317
00:19:34.485 --> 00:19:37.124
I tried so hard to make him dirty...

318
00:19:37.695 --> 00:19:41.025
when he was a pure engineering student for more than seven years.

319
00:19:43.195 --> 00:19:44.394
But I got it wrong.

320
00:19:45.894 --> 00:19:47.465
I guess he can't be changed.

321
00:19:47.705 --> 00:19:50.034
Then why don't you just ask him to marry you?

322
00:19:50.735 --> 00:19:51.735
Are you crazy?

323
00:19:51.735 --> 00:19:54.705
Why not? The person who wants to get married fast should say it.

324
00:19:55.144 --> 00:19:56.515
I don't want to.

325
00:19:58.374 --> 00:20:00.284
I don't want to seem desperate.

326
00:20:07.425 --> 00:20:09.255
- A marriage proposal? - That's right.

327
00:20:09.255 --> 00:20:11.894
Listen. She wanted a sofa, and a matrimonial home,

328
00:20:11.894 --> 00:20:15.495
and talked about her colleague. That means she wants to get married...

329
00:20:15.495 --> 00:20:18.695
like her colleague in a matrimonial home where she can put the sofa.

330
00:20:19.665 --> 00:20:20.834
That must be it.

331
00:20:22.465 --> 00:20:24.475
No, that's not true. No way.

332
00:20:24.505 --> 00:20:27.675
What do you mean? I thought you've been seeing her for seven years.

333
00:20:28.044 --> 00:20:29.405
People normally get married after that long.

334
00:20:29.405 --> 00:20:33.144
Sang Goo, Ho Rang is not an ordinary girl.

335
00:20:33.445 --> 00:20:35.515
Do you know what she did for me when I was writing my thesis paper?

336
00:20:35.515 --> 00:20:38.485
She looked after my professor's dog when he went on a vacation.

337
00:20:38.685 --> 00:20:40.854
And she even helped with his kids' homework.

338
00:20:41.054 --> 00:20:44.725
She must know well what an important phase I'm going through now.

339
00:20:44.755 --> 00:20:48.564
Marriage? Gosh, you're only saying that because you don't know her.

340
00:20:49.665 --> 00:20:52.665
Oh, my goodness. We missed that part.

341
00:20:54.505 --> 00:20:58.175
She's mad because the sofa used to be displayed in the shop.

342
00:21:02.905 --> 00:21:03.975
My gosh.

343
00:21:05.844 --> 00:21:08.644
- That must be it. That's it. - That's right.

344
00:21:08.715 --> 00:21:10.255
How did you figure that out?

345
00:21:10.255 --> 00:21:11.955
Gosh, we missed that part.

346
00:21:12.915 --> 00:21:14.155
My gosh.

347
00:21:14.554 --> 00:21:17.695
- Gosh, it's bitter. - Have this soup.

348
00:21:19.794 --> 00:21:21.564
It's because it was displayed.

349
00:21:32.534 --> 00:21:34.644
Yes, Mom.

350
00:21:35.074 --> 00:21:36.874
- Aren't you sleeping? - What is it?

351
00:21:37.844 --> 00:21:39.715
Are you coming tomorrow morning?

352
00:21:39.884 --> 00:21:40.945
Yes.

353
00:21:41.544 --> 00:21:44.215
Oh, it's just...

354
00:21:44.354 --> 00:21:46.685
I had something to talk about with the meeting tomorrow.

355
00:21:47.554 --> 00:21:49.624
Is this Ji Ho? What is it?

356
00:21:53.165 --> 00:21:54.864
Dad, where's Mom?

357
00:21:55.064 --> 00:21:57.935
I don't know. She just passed the phone to me.

358
00:21:58.094 --> 00:22:00.005
What is it? Did something happen?

359
00:22:00.804 --> 00:22:01.864
It's...

360
00:22:07.344 --> 00:22:09.675
Okay, Dad. Safe trip tomorrow.

361
00:22:09.874 --> 00:22:10.915
Okay.

362
00:22:12.044 --> 00:22:13.384
- You're here. - Yes.

363
00:22:14.485 --> 00:22:16.614
- Was it your dad? - Yes.

364
00:22:17.054 --> 00:22:20.525
I told him that we're not going to have a wedding.

365
00:22:21.685 --> 00:22:23.124
I did too.

366
00:22:23.495 --> 00:22:25.124
- Oh, really? - Yes.

367
00:22:25.394 --> 00:22:27.124
I thought it'd be better to tell this ahead,

368
00:22:27.124 --> 00:22:29.225
so nothing special will happen tomorrow.

369
00:22:30.394 --> 00:22:33.405
Did your parents take it well?

370
00:22:33.765 --> 00:22:34.804
Yes, they did.

371
00:22:35.505 --> 00:22:36.574
Thankfully,

372
00:22:37.205 --> 00:22:40.175
Dad didn't have much to say about it.

373
00:22:40.604 --> 00:22:43.344
I think it's because my brother hasn't had a wedding yet.

374
00:22:43.344 --> 00:22:45.275
- I think that helped a little. - I see.

375
00:22:45.975 --> 00:22:48.245
My mother didn't say much too.

376
00:22:48.415 --> 00:22:51.985
I think the actual price of wedding must have shocked her much.

377
00:22:53.824 --> 00:22:54.985
That's great.

378
00:22:55.384 --> 00:22:56.854
Well,

379
00:22:57.495 --> 00:22:59.354
after the meeting tomorrow,

380
00:22:59.455 --> 00:23:02.394
there won't be any other expenses, right?

381
00:23:02.465 --> 00:23:03.534
Yes.

382
00:23:03.695 --> 00:23:06.134
After tomorrow,

383
00:23:06.364 --> 00:23:08.564
let's wrap up with the final contract.

384
00:23:08.705 --> 00:23:09.705
Sure.

385
00:23:11.935 --> 00:23:14.905
By the way, how did your mother react?

386
00:23:15.604 --> 00:23:17.415
What does your mother think?

387
00:23:18.344 --> 00:23:20.185
- Pardon? - I've thought about it,

388
00:23:20.515 --> 00:23:22.784
and realized your mother...

389
00:23:23.155 --> 00:23:25.354
had no special opinion from the last time we saw her.

390
00:23:29.755 --> 00:23:31.755
My mom...

391
00:23:34.564 --> 00:23:37.394
My mom usually doesn't have much opinion.

392
00:23:38.235 --> 00:23:41.405
I told you already that our family is totally patriarchal.

393
00:23:43.804 --> 00:23:47.775
Talking about opinions, I think your father has not much too.

394
00:23:48.675 --> 00:23:51.015
- What does your father think? - I'm not interested.

395
00:23:52.544 --> 00:23:53.614
Sorry?

396
00:23:54.515 --> 00:23:57.755
At 5pm tomorrow? I'll be at the bus terminal then.

397
00:23:57.955 --> 00:23:59.155
Okay.

398
00:23:59.655 --> 00:24:02.054
Wear thick clothes since it's cold in Seoul.

399
00:24:02.255 --> 00:24:03.425
Of course!

400
00:24:03.755 --> 00:24:06.155
Mom, don't forget to take medicine for nausea.

401
00:24:08.195 --> 00:24:09.894
Why isn't mom saying anything?

402
00:24:12.165 --> 00:24:13.864
She even put Dad on the phone.

403
00:24:20.044 --> 00:24:21.745
Mom, are you sleeping?

404
00:24:22.475 --> 00:24:23.614
I am sleeping.

405
00:24:26.644 --> 00:24:29.745
How can she message me back if she's asleep?

406
00:24:39.354 --> 00:24:40.465
What is it?

407
00:24:41.195 --> 00:24:43.495
It feels like she's holding a grudge against me.

408
00:24:49.564 --> 00:24:53.205
Marriage is a major life event.

409
00:24:53.804 --> 00:24:56.374
We are now in a very special relationship.

410
00:24:57.515 --> 00:25:00.614
Speaking of which, why don't I pour you a glass?

411
00:25:00.614 --> 00:25:02.884
- That sounds good. - Okay.

412
00:25:05.054 --> 00:25:08.384
Don't you think our kids are smart?

413
00:25:08.384 --> 00:25:11.955
I was a bit sad when they said they didn't want a wedding ceremony.

414
00:25:12.094 --> 00:25:14.265
But everyone is feeling the recession these days.

415
00:25:14.265 --> 00:25:16.765
I think they are very sensible.

416
00:25:16.765 --> 00:25:20.205
I'm glad you think that way.

417
00:25:22.405 --> 00:25:24.104
- Let me pour you a one. - Thanks.

418
00:25:26.235 --> 00:25:27.945
I appreciate it.

419
00:25:28.304 --> 00:25:31.215
I can imagine her being really smart...

420
00:25:31.574 --> 00:25:34.284
to get into Seoul University all the way from Namhae.

421
00:25:34.915 --> 00:25:37.985
That's not true. She's just like everybody else.

422
00:25:38.715 --> 00:25:41.324
She's very polite too.

423
00:25:41.955 --> 00:25:43.695
Yes, like everybody else.

424
00:25:44.155 --> 00:25:46.155
Not like the young ones these days,

425
00:25:46.155 --> 00:25:49.195
she's so innocent and kind.

426
00:25:50.695 --> 00:25:51.794
That's not true.

427
00:25:53.334 --> 00:25:54.935
She's just like everybody else.

428
00:25:57.334 --> 00:25:58.534
I see.

429
00:25:58.534 --> 00:25:59.775
She's just the same as everybody else.

430
00:26:00.005 --> 00:26:03.314
She is immature like everyone in her age.

431
00:26:03.374 --> 00:26:05.614
She is also a bit selfish.

432
00:26:06.044 --> 00:26:07.544
She's just one of the young ones.

433
00:26:07.685 --> 00:26:08.884
I don't think she's different from them.

434
00:26:10.955 --> 00:26:12.054
Okay.

435
00:26:12.314 --> 00:26:14.655
You shouldn't have said something unnecessary like that.

436
00:26:17.695 --> 00:26:21.465
Please let me pour you a glass too.

437
00:26:21.665 --> 00:26:22.725
That sounds good.

438
00:26:22.725 --> 00:26:24.064
It's a great day today.

439
00:26:26.294 --> 00:26:27.405
Right?

440
00:26:34.245 --> 00:26:35.705
Thank you.

441
00:26:35.874 --> 00:26:37.175
Did you pay for it?

442
00:26:37.515 --> 00:26:38.574
Yes.

443
00:26:38.874 --> 00:26:41.644
I've read that it's better to pay for the first family meeting...

444
00:26:41.715 --> 00:26:43.584
before leaving the place.

445
00:26:46.284 --> 00:26:49.084
Should we calculate everything at the end of every month?

446
00:26:49.084 --> 00:26:52.054
Splitting every time is a bit of hassle.

447
00:26:52.124 --> 00:26:54.824
Today will be the last time we need to pay for things anyway.

448
00:26:55.564 --> 00:26:57.534
Let me take care of this today.

449
00:26:57.534 --> 00:26:58.634
No, you can't.

450
00:26:59.165 --> 00:27:00.564
This is an expensive place.

451
00:27:00.564 --> 00:27:03.975
Your parents had to come all the way to Seoul.

452
00:27:04.475 --> 00:27:08.144
We have to count their transportation expenses and efforts.

453
00:27:09.245 --> 00:27:10.344
I see.

454
00:27:24.955 --> 00:27:28.894
We just need to announce and introduce each other's families.

455
00:27:29.794 --> 00:27:33.134
It's just taking several steps and things are done.

456
00:27:33.665 --> 00:27:37.804
Getting married is actually easier than I thought.

457
00:27:38.935 --> 00:27:41.005
Honestly, I was worried...

458
00:27:41.445 --> 00:27:44.314
because I thought my family wouldn't take things well.

459
00:27:44.915 --> 00:27:47.344
I knew it was going to be this easy.

460
00:27:47.814 --> 00:27:49.854
- Really? - Yes.

461
00:27:51.084 --> 00:27:53.824
We are quite a good combination of two people.

462
00:27:57.324 --> 00:27:59.794
Although on loan, I have a house.

463
00:28:00.495 --> 00:28:03.665
You went to a good university, but you don't have a job.

464
00:28:03.965 --> 00:28:06.834
I'm sure those play a part in their decision making.

465
00:28:07.665 --> 00:28:09.874
I agree with the former one.

466
00:28:10.275 --> 00:28:11.675
But what do you mean by the latter one?

467
00:28:11.675 --> 00:28:15.405
They want someone well-educated as the family of teachers.

468
00:28:15.975 --> 00:28:19.985
But they don't want to look up to their daughter-in-law.

469
00:28:20.215 --> 00:28:22.215
You satisfied my parents' hypocritical needs...

470
00:28:22.384 --> 00:28:24.515
unintentionally.

471
00:28:26.255 --> 00:28:29.324
I never thought me being unemployed as a graduate of a good school...

472
00:28:29.624 --> 00:28:32.324
could bring such a great synergy effect.

473
00:28:33.265 --> 00:28:34.425
That's a good thing.

474
00:28:34.525 --> 00:28:35.824
I'm glad.

475
00:28:44.235 --> 00:28:45.405
What?

476
00:28:45.935 --> 00:28:47.574
What did I say?

477
00:28:49.275 --> 00:28:52.215
Why are you like this today?

478
00:28:53.884 --> 00:28:55.284
Are you drunk?

479
00:29:00.124 --> 00:29:02.485
Yes, I am. I'm a little bit drunk.

480
00:29:03.195 --> 00:29:05.854
I'd love to say what I want to say since I'm a bit drunk.

481
00:29:06.124 --> 00:29:10.864
We don't want to marry off our daughter in such a way.

482
00:29:12.634 --> 00:29:14.304
What do you mean by that?

483
00:29:14.364 --> 00:29:16.675
I want them to do what everybody else does.

484
00:29:16.675 --> 00:29:18.205
I want them to have a wedding.

485
00:29:19.435 --> 00:29:21.874
They finished talking about it all.

486
00:29:21.874 --> 00:29:23.215
We think the same.

487
00:29:23.574 --> 00:29:26.175
They should have a wedding.

488
00:29:42.294 --> 00:29:44.394
Have you gone senile?

489
00:29:44.534 --> 00:29:46.465
Are you sick or something?

490
00:29:47.604 --> 00:29:49.935
My menopause is right around the corner.

491
00:29:51.705 --> 00:29:53.604
Why are you like this?

492
00:29:53.604 --> 00:29:56.614
Do you want to ruin your own daughter's marriage?

493
00:29:56.975 --> 00:29:59.814
What am I ruining?

494
00:30:00.284 --> 00:30:04.084
They sounded cocky first.

495
00:30:04.155 --> 00:30:05.584
What did they say?

496
00:30:05.584 --> 00:30:07.755
They are such nice people.

497
00:30:07.755 --> 00:30:09.485
They said she wasn't like the other young ones.

498
00:30:10.294 --> 00:30:13.025
They said she was innocent and kind.

499
00:30:13.025 --> 00:30:15.064
That's a compliment for a woman.

500
00:30:15.064 --> 00:30:18.495
They said it's better for her to stay home and raise a kid...

501
00:30:19.235 --> 00:30:21.534
since it costs more if they both work.

502
00:30:21.935 --> 00:30:23.675
That's actually true.

503
00:30:25.505 --> 00:30:26.745
Besides,

504
00:30:27.505 --> 00:30:29.405
how could they think she looked like me?

505
00:30:33.344 --> 00:30:35.715
You and Ji Ho look exactly the same.

506
00:30:36.854 --> 00:30:38.755
Did you not know that?

507
00:30:45.779 --> 00:30:49.011
